## ğŸ”„ How It Works

**Step-by-Step Flow:**

1. ğŸ“¤ User uploads an MRI scan (JPG, PNG, JPEG)
2. ğŸ–¼ï¸ Frontend displays image preview
3. ğŸš€ User clicks "Classify Tumor" button
4. ğŸ“¡ Image sent to Flask backend (`POST /predict`)
5. ğŸ”§ Backend preprocesses: resize â†’ normalize â†’ format
6. ğŸ¤– TensorFlow model runs inference
7. ğŸ“Š Model outputs 4 probabilities (softmax)
8. ğŸ¯ Backend selects highest confidence class
9. ğŸ“‹ Backend fetches educational info & specialist
10. âœ… JSON response sent back to frontend
11. ğŸ“¸ Results displayed with confidence percentage

---

## ğŸ§¬ Model Details

**Architecture:** VGG16 Transfer Learning  
**Input Size:** 150 Ã— 150 pixels (RGB)  
**Output:** 4 classes (softmax probabilities)  
**Training Tech:**
- Base: VGG16 (pre-trained on ImageNet, frozen layers)
- Custom Head: Dense(512) â†’ Dropout(0.5) â†’ Dense(4)
- Optimizer: Adam
- Loss: Categorical Crossentropy
- Epochs: 37 (with data augmentation)

**Data Augmentation:**
- Rotation: Â±50Â°
- Shifts: Â±25% width/height
- Shear: Â±25%
- Zoom: Â±25%
- Horizontal flip: Yes

